# Fix compilation warnings

**Policy:** Every change must leave the tree **warning-free**. Do not finish a task while `cargo build`, `cargo test --lib`, or **`cargo qcheck`** still report warnings you introduced or exposed.

## What to run

1. **`cargo qcheck`** — Clippy on all targets/features (project alias; see `.cargo/config.toml`).
2. **`cargo build`** and/or **`cargo test --lib`** when you touched code paths Clippy does not cover or when the user reported **rustc** warnings (`unused_imports`, `dead_code`, `unused_variables`, …).

Treat **warnings like errors** for work you ship in the same turn.

## How to fix (prefer real fixes)

| Warning | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| **`unused_imports`** | Remove the import; or use the item; do not re-export unused public names. |
| **`dead_code`** / unused fn | Delete if truly obsolete; **`#[cfg(test)]`** if only tests need it; wire it through production if it should exist. |
| **`unused_variables`** | Remove, prefix with `_` only when intentionally ignored, or use the value. |
| **Clippy** | Refactor per [clippy-no-suppress.mdc](clippy-no-suppress.mdc) — no new **`#[allow(…)]`**. |

## Do not

- Add **`#[allow(dead_code)]`**, **`#[allow(unused)]`**, or broad **`#![allow(…)]`** to silence new warnings.
- Leave “harmless” warnings for a follow-up when you can fix them in the same change.
- Export types or functions “for later” that nothing uses.

## Rare exceptions

Local, commented **`#[allow(…)]`** only when rustc/Clippy cannot be satisfied otherwise (e.g. **`include!`** glue). Document **why** in the comment. Existing legacy allows are debt — remove when you touch that code.

## Before ending the turn

- [ ] `cargo qcheck` — no new Clippy warnings.
- [ ] `cargo build` / `cargo test --lib` — no new rustc warnings from your edits.
- [ ] No new warning suppressions unless the rare-exception case above applies.
